<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcfc8896a-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2152"><num value="2152">§ 2152.</num><heading> Intervention in litigation</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc8896b-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2152/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Intervention</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Oversight Board may intervene in any litigation filed against the territorial government.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc8896c-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2152/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Injunctive relief</heading><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc8896d-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2152/b/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">If the Oversight Board intervenes in a litigation under subsection (a), the Oversight Board may seek injunctive relief, including a stay of litigation.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc8896e-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2152/b/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> No independent basis for relief</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">This section does not create an independent basis on which injunctive relief, including a stay of litigation, may be granted.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idcfc8896f-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/pl/114/187/tII/s212">Pub. L. 114–187, title II, § 212</ref>, <date date="2016-06-30">June 30, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/577">130 Stat. 577</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
